<topic id="apply-profiling-conditional-set">
  <title>Applying Profiling Condition Sets</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Author editing mode<indexterm>Apply profiling condition
          sets</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>XML documents<indexterm>Author Mode editing<indexterm>Apply profiling condition
              sets</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Apply profiling condition sets in Author Mode</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>All defined <xref href="condition-sets-management.dita#condition-sets-management">Profiling
        Condition Sets</xref> are available as shortcuts in the <xref
        href="../topics/profiling-conditional-text-menu.dita#profiling-conditional-text-menu"
        format="dita"><uicontrol><image href="../img/ProfilingToolbar16.png" id="image_v2c_s4f_wr"
          />Profiling / Conditional Text</uicontrol> toolbar menu</xref>. Select a menu entry to
      apply the condition set. The filtered content is then grayed-out in the
        <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode and <xref href="outliner-view.dita#outliner-view"
          ><uicontrol>Outline</uicontrol> view</xref>. An element is filtered-out when one of its
      attributes is part of the condition set and its value does not match any of the values covered
      by the condition set.</p>
